      "description": "Simulated velocity magnitude fields compared against particle image velocimetry (PIV) data in the pump volute region. Agreement within 8% for 90th-percentile velocity magnitudes. Uncertainty in experimental data discussed qualitatively; measurement repeatability across three pump specimens noted in the test report, with variability attributed to manufacturing tolerances and flow conditioning differences.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-02-velocity-piv-uq"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-03-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Normalized index of hemolysis comparison at worst-case operating point",
      "description": "Computational normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro hemolysis measurements at the identified worst-case operating condition (6 L/min, 3500 RPM). CFD NIH of 0.0032 g/100L versus experimental NIH of 0.0038 g/100L. Aleatory variability in experimental hemolysis measurements arises from biological variability in blood samples, inter-specimen differences, and assay precision. These sources of variability are discussed in the experimental protocol documentation and acknowledged in the credibility assessment narrative; however, no formal UQ artifact has been linked to this result. The assessment team considered the variability acceptable given the conservative acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and the consistency of repeated experimental runs."
    },
    {
